    <string name="weather_about_uv_index">The UV index is a measure of the level of ultraviolet radiation. The values of the index range from zero upward - the higher the UV index, the greater the potential for damage to the skin and eye, and the less time it takes for harm to occur</string>
    <string name="text_scale">Scale</string>
    <string name="weather_about_humidity">Humidity is the concentration of water vapor present in the air. Water vapor, the gaseous state of water, is generally invisible to the naked eye. Humidity indicates the likelihood for precipitation, dew, or fog to be present</string>
    <string name="text_average_for_day">Average for the day</string>
    <string name="weather_about_dewpoint">The dew point temperature is an important measure of humidity. As the dew point reaches 20 C/70 F degrees, almost everyone feels \"sticky\". Thus the dew point is the best predictor of energy use for cooling in the summer</string>
    <string name="weather_visibility_about">Visibility indicates how far you can clearly see outdoors before objects become obscured by weather or atmospheric conditions</string>
