    <string name="weather_about_pressure">Mean sea level pressure, a measure of how much the atmosphere is pressing down, adjusted to sea level. Watching how it changes can provide an early indication of weather changes. Pressure falling usually means unsettled weather is approaching, while pressure rising often means conditions are becoming more stable</string>
